The General Administration Department has agreed to the selection list of the year 2022-23 prepared by this department for temporary promotion from Maharashtra Agricultural Service, Group-A (Deputy Director of Agriculture) cadre to Maharashtra Agricultural Service, Group-A (Superintending Agricultural Officer) cadre. Sadar

As per the agreement, the following officers will be posted as Group-A (Deputy Director of Agriculture) (Pay Scale S-20: Rs. 56100 - 177500) from the cadre in the interest of public service and administration.

In terms of convenience, Maharashtra Agricultural Service, Group-A (Superintending Agriculture Officer) (Pay Scale S-23: Rs. 67700 - 208700) is approved under this Government Order for appointment to the following posts in this cadre with net provisional promotion: -

As per the provision in the 1/8/2019, the names of the officers concerned will be removed from the selection list of the year 2022-23 and their eligibility will be checked for provisional promotion to the post of Maharashtra Agricultural Service, Group-A in the third year's selection list (year 2025-26) without considering their names in the selection list to be held in the next two years (year 2023-24 and 2024-25).

(d) the temporary promotion of such officers to the post of Maharashtra Agricultural Service, Group-A is being granted subject to the assumption that no departmental inquiry of any kind has been instituted or proposed to be instituted against such officers as on the date of the said order.

(e) the aforesaid officers to be transferred to the nearest senior officer of the Department in charge of their present office and to join the post of Promotional Officer with immediate effect. It is also brought to the notice that the Government Notification of the General Administration Department has been issued. As per the provision in the 21/6/2021, the officers concerned are required to join the post of promotion within 30 days from the date of issue of this order.
3. The inter-service superiority of the above officers shall be as per the approval of the General Administration Department to the selection list of the year 2022-23.
4. The Commissioner (Agriculture), Maharashtra State, Pune shall see to it that the said orders come into force with immediate effect.
By order and in the name of the Governor of Maharashtra.
